[4] Wisconsin (Oconto County): deer
Date: 12 Jan 2022 8:15 a.m. CST
Source: We Are Green Bay [edited]
https://www.wearegreenbay.com/news/local-news/deer-tests-positive-for-cwd-in-oconto-co-3-year-baiting-feeding-ban/


The State's Department of Natural Resources (DNR) has revealed reports of a deer in the Town of Underhill tested positive for CWD [chronic wasting disease].

This is the 1st deer in Oconto County to confirm to have CWD, according to the release.

The deer was a one-year-old hunter-harvested buck taken during the 2021 gun deer season. The information was released on Tue 11 Jan [2022] and detail what the DNR will be doing to protect the area.

According to state law, a 3-year baiting and feeding ban will be placed in Oconto County. There will also be a 2-year ban in Menominee County, as the deer with CWD was collected within 10 mi [16.1 km] of the county line.

Shawano County would have had a 2-year ban, as it is within 10 mi [16.1 km] of the county line, but the county already has a 2-year baiting and feeding ban following the discovery of a deer with CWD as well.

[Byline: Gunner Teixeira]

